<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-87-0162 </DOCNO><TEXT>The nonlinear differential equations describing the problem of shock wavestructure in a two-component gas mixture are reduced to a system of twocoupled nonlinear differential equations. This system is solved numericallyusing the finite-difference method. It is found that the relative shockwave thickness of the mixture increases with the increase of ratio betweenthe viscosity coefficients when the ratio between the mass fractionsis costant.</TEXT></DOC>